      must have sheltered it carefully.";
    ],
    before [;
      Smell: <<Smell Basil>>;
      Taste: <<Taste Basil>>;
    ],
    has
  ;


Herb -> -> -> Basil "basil"                                             ! >Basil
  with
    name 'basil',
    description "A cluster of large green leaves with pointed tips.",
    before [;
      Smell: "It's strong and peppery, with notes of anise.";
      Taste:
        "You try a single leaf: it's sharp at first,
        then peppery and a bit like licorice.";
    ],
    herb_text
      "Basil: difficult to grow in these northern climes, but common in
      warmer lands like southern France and especially Tuscany, where it
      is prized as both culinary herb and remedy. Effective for digestive
      troubles and inflammation of the eyes.",
  has
    ;


! -------------------------------------------------------- Restricted Garden

Object -> GardenGate "restricted garden gate"                      ! >GardenGate
  class AdjObject,
  with
    adj_name 'restricted' 'garden',
    noun_name 'gate',
    when_open "The gate for the restricted garden is open.",
    when_closed [;
      print "The gate for the restricted garden is closed";
      if (self has locked) print " and locked";
      ".";
    ],
    before [;
      Unlock:
        if (second == GardenGateKey) {
          give self ~locked;
          give self open;
          print "You unlock the gate, open it, and enter the smaller garden.^^";
          PlayerTo(RestrictedGarden);
          rtrue;
        }
    ],
    description "A wooden fence protecting access to the dangerous plants.",
    found_in RestrictedGarden Garden,
    door_dir (w_to) (e_to),
    with_key GardenGateKey
  has
    static door openable locked lockable;


Object GardenGateKey "iron key"                                 ! >GardenGateKey
  class AdjObject,
  with
    article "an",
    adj_name 'iron' 'garden' 'pitted' 'rusty',
    noun_name 'key',
    description
      "A heavy iron key, its surface pitted and darkened with rust from
      years hanging in the damp herbarium. It opens the gate to the
      restricted garden where the dangerous herbs grow.",
    has ok_carry;


Room RestrictedGarden "Restricted Garden"                    ! >RestrictedGarden
  with
    description [;
      print
        "Here is Aelred's collection of dangerous plants---those
        too potent for casual use, too deadly for error. The beds here
        are smaller, more carefully separated.";
      if (self hasnt general)
        print
          "^^Aelred brought you here only twice, making you repeat each plant's
          name, its use, its danger. ~Respect them, my son~, he said. ~In the
          right dose, they heal. In the wrong, they kill.~^";
      give self general;
      rtrue;
    ],
    e_to GardenGate,
    out_to GardenGate,
  has
    ;


Object -> RestBeds "beds"                                            ! >RestBeds
  with
    name 'beds' 'bed',
    description [;
      print
        "Small, carefully separated beds---no risk of cross-contamination.
        You recognize monkshood by its dark leaves and hooded flowers,
        foxglove by its pink bells, henbane by its sickly-sweet smell";
      if (MandrakeRoot hasnt moved) print
        ". A small gnarled mandrake root pushes from the earth, pale and
        forked like a tiny human figure";
      ".";
    ],
    before [;
      Receive:
        "Soon, it will be your daily labor to plant things
        here---but not yet. Not today.";
    ],
  has
    pluralname scenery container open;


Plant -> -> MonkshoodPlant "monkshood plant"                   ! >MonkshoodPlant
  with
    name 'monkshood',
    description
      "Several feet high, with spikes of helmet-shaped, deep blue or
      violet flowers that resemble a monk's cowl.",
    herb_text
      "Monk's Hood: when used with caution, can
      reduce inflammation or problems with breathing. When used without care,
      can result in a death that looks like rabies: with frothy saliva,
      and impaired vision. Used as a liniment or tincture.",
    before [;
      Smell:
        "You cautiously sniff---barely any scent at all. The plant saves
        its power for those who consume it.";
      Taste: "You dare not. It can be lethal even in small doses.";
    ]
  has toxic ;


